      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "I'M A SOULMAN (3) comes here third-up and ready to strike following a good performance in a much stronger race at Pinjarra most recently. Faithfull rides from the good draw and he shouldn't be too far off the speed. He's clearly the one to beat with the form he brings into this. LEAFICE (10) was a touch disappointing at Pinjarra when out to 1400m last time out and drops back to 1100m today. Drawn nicely and her form suggests she's a leading chance in this event. LONGTIMEBELIEVER (5) hadn't been far away prior to finishing 5.5 lengths adrift in eighth last start over 1100m at Albany. Will appreciate the drop in grade. Well placed and is one of the contenders. DEW TELL (8) was out of the money when resuming from a spell last start over 1000m at Belmont Park, beaten 4 lengths. Strips fitter and should be thereabouts. FLICK'N RUBIES (9) can be thereabouts with the blinkers on first time.",
